2.6 We recommended and management agreed to implement the following
measures to assure the reliability of balances of PPE accounts:
 Designation of a Property Custodian and Creation of Inventory
Committee to undertake the inventory taking;
 Physical inventory of fixed assets shall be made at least once a year;
 Establishment of property identification and coding;
 Maintenance of the Acknowledgement Receipt of Equipment to
establish the official accountable for the property;
 Reconciliation of the inventory report with the balances reflected in
the financial statements, identification of persons accountable for loss
of property, and proper adjustment in the financial statements, if any;
and
 Maintenance of updated Property Card and Property Plant and
Equipment Ledger Cards.

We have recommended that management:
 Justify the absence of local ordinance creating the LDRRM Office;
 Submit the LDRRMF Utilization Report and ensure that implementation should be based on the planned program/projects identified during the budget process

