In view of the foregoing observations, we have recommended the following:
 That Management grants cash advances only for payment of salaries and wages, honoraria and other petty operating expenses. Claims above ₱15,000.00 should be made through checks;
 Purchases of supplies and materials be made through the prescribed modes under RA 9184 and not through cash advances. Likewise, in no case shall payment of implemented projects be made out of cash advances as the same should be made directly to the suppliers or contractors;
 In all instances, no additional cash advances shall be granted unless previous ones are liquidated or duly accounted for; and
 The Municipal Mayor looks into the possibility of withholding the salaries and claims of officials and employees who fail to account or liquidate their cash advance.

In view of the foregoing observations, we have recommended that Management:
 Justify the non-creation of LDRRM Office;
 Submit the LDRRMFIP and ensure that implementation should be based from planned program/projects identified during the budget process;
 Make a report on the fund status and utilization of the LDRRMF and post it in conspicuous places of the municipality. This is to promote transparency and to prevent suspicions of any irregularity; and
 Appropriate funds for the procurement of rescue equipment will last longer and thus provide more benefit to the constituents.

We have recommended that management implement the following measures to assure the reliability of balances of PPE Accounts:
(a) Physical inventory of fixed assets shall be made at least once a year;
(b) Establishment of property identification and coding;
(c) Maintenance of the Acknowledgement Receipt of Equipment to establish the official/employee accountable for the property;
(d) Reconciliation of the inventory report with the balances reflected in the financial statements, identification of persons accountable for loss of property, and proper adjustment in the financial statements;
(e) Maintenance of updated Property Card and Property Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards.

We have recommended the following:

The Municipal Treasurer should be granted only cash advances for payroll, honoraria and petty operating expenses;
A petty cash fund should be established for operating expenses of small amount;
Claims above P 15,000.00 should be made through checks;
Cash advance for payment of operational expenses should not be granted unless breakdown of expenses be attached to support the disbursement vouchers; and
Additional cash advances should not be granted unless previous ones are properly liquidated or accounted for.  Management should enforce liquidation of cash advances in accordance to pertinent provisions of COA Circular 97-002.

In view of the foregoing observations, we have recommended that Management:

Justify the non-creation of LDRRM Office;
Submit the LDRRMFIP and ensure that implementation should be based from planned program/projects identified during the budget process;
Special trust fund shall be maintained solely for LDRRMF.  The accountant should record in appropriate books the unexpended balance of the LDRRMF to properly track the utilization of the fund.

In view of the foregoing, we have recommended that the management:

Justify the above noted observations;
Revisit DILG-DBM Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2011-1 on the expenditure items not covered or are prohibited to be paid out of the 20% Development Fund for guidance;
Submit the required Utilization Report.

